Eden started life as a whaling community and remains a vital fishing town with a population of over 3000.

The fishing town of Eden is at the northern head of the large (3,100 ha) Twofold Bay. Entrance depth into bay is 36 metres. Width of bay is 5 km wide. Bottom sand. MHWS 1.6m. MLWS 0.3m. VHF Channels 16, port working channel 8.

Eden town has a straight forward grid layout with a bustling main street running thru the center. Walking from one end (the main Wharf) to the other, (the Country Golf Club) will take you approx; half'n hour.  There is a taxi service to get you around and bus services to take you out of town.  For water explorers there are a number of cruise boats ready to take you around the bay.
